{"title":"Pro Bike Check: Tom Pidcock’s Pinarello Dogma XC HT Short Track Bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/tom-pidcocks-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-pro-bike-check/","date":1691756882000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check.jpg\" alt=\"tom pidcock pinarello dogman xc hardtail world champs short track pro bike check\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check.jpg 1600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Yesterday’s 2023 UCI XCC Short Track World Championships proved to be as controversial as it was exciting. While French rider, Pauline Ferrand-Prévot, stormed to victory aboard the all-new Pinarello Dogma XC HT, her INEOS Grenadiers team mate, Tom Pidcock, rode the same to a Bronze medal. No mention of Tom and yesterday’s Short Track is complete without mention of the event that took place in the final turn…</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<div><blockquote><div> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/reel/CvxiYL9rwI1/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" target=\"_blank\"> <div> <div></div> <div> <div></div> <div></div></div></div><div></div> <div></div><div> <div>View this post on Instagram</div></div><div></div> <div><div> <div></div> <div></div> <div></div></div><div> <div></div> <div></div></div><div> <div></div> <div></div> <div></div></div></div> <div> <div></div> <div></div></div></a><p><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/reel/CvxiYL9rwI1/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" target=\"_blank\">A post shared by Luca Schwarzbauer (@luca_schwarzbauer)</a></p></div></blockquote></div>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The British rider made unintended contact with Germany’s Luca Schwarzbauer as he slipped through a small gap left open by Schwarzbauer on the inside of the final turn. As a result, Luca lost rear wheel traction, forcing a low side crash. He conceded the position to Tom, who went on to secure 3rd place. New Zealand’s Sam Gaze took the Gold medal, with Frenchman Victor Koretzky taking Silver. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Back to the bikes…</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Indeed, yesterday was the first time the new Pinarello Dogma XC HT has graced the race track. This particular race track is nowhere near as rough as some we’ve seen on the World Cup circuit this season, and so it wasn’t too much of a surprise to see a number of riders opting to use a hardtail.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Without further ado, let’s take a closer look at Tom’s Dogma XC HT, and how it has been set up by his mechanic, Arune Kristensen.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"tom pidcock pinarello dogman xc hardtail world champs short track pro bike check\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Pro Bike Check: Tom Pidcock’s Pinarello Dogma XC HT</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Rider: Tom Pidcock</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Age: 24</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Nationality: British</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Height: 170 cm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>2023 Season Best Result: 1st at UCI World Cup XC, Nové Město</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Fresh off the back of the Tour de France, Tom Pidcock is switching gears this week for his assault on the 2023 UCI XCO World Championships in Scotland. As discussed, Tom’s week got off to a good start with a 3rd place finish in Short Track, giving him a front row start for Saturday’s XCO Final. Not that this man necessarily <em>needs</em> a front row start… </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-world-champs-short-track-pro-bike-check-assymetric-seat-stays.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcock-pinarello-dogma-xc-hard