ogma-xc-ht-pro-bike-check.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcok-pro-bike-check-2023-uci-world-champs-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-non-plus-hubs.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcok-pro-bike-check-2023-uci-world-champs-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-non-plus-hubs-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"tom pidcok pinarello hardtail non plus hubset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcok-pro-bike-check-2023-uci-world-champs-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-non-plus-hubs-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcok-pro-bike-check-2023-uci-world-champs-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-non-plus-hubs-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcok-pro-bike-check-2023-uci-world-champs-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-non-plus-hubs-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcok-pro-bike-check-2023-uci-world-champs-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-non-plus-hubs-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcok-pro-bike-check-2023-uci-world-champs-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-non-plus-hubs-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcok-pro-bike-check-2023-uci-world-champs-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-non-plus-hubs-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/tom-pidcok-pro-bike-check-2023-uci-world-champs-pinarello-dogma-xc-hardtail-non-plus-hubs.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In the cockpit, Tom runs the Most Talon Ultra XC handlebar-stem combo at a width of 690mm with a 110mm reach and a negative 17° offset, with ESI grips. While a lot of XC riders are preferring 4-piston brakes, Tom relies upon the Shimano XTR 2-piston brakes for speed management, paired with 160mm Shimano Ice Technologies FREEZA rotors.</p>\n\n\n\n<div><div><div><div><figure><img srcset=